}

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

To find the greatest common factor of some numbers, one method is to prime factor each number:

    [`` [$num1] = [$num1Output] ``]

    [`` [$num2] = [$num2Output] ``]

    [`` [$num3] = [$num3Output] ``]

[$output]

    [`` [$ansFactorList] ``]

So the greatest common factor of [`[$num1]`], [`[$num2]`] and [`[$num3]`] is [`[$ans]`].

